From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 08 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] usb: typec: tcpm: force DP mux at SRC_READY for passive
 USB-C→DP cable

A passive USB-C→DisplayPort cable connects a self-powered DP display
(which sources 5 V on Vbus) but has no USB PD controller.  Every
Source_Capabilities transmission returns TCPC_TX_FAILED (no GoodCRC)
so pd_capable stays false after nCapsCount retries.  Without a PD
session there are no VDMs, so the displayport.c altmode driver never
runs and the typec mux stays in TYPEC_STATE_USB forever.

Detect this case at SRC_READY:
  - pd_capable == false: no GoodCRC was ever received
  - vbus_present == true: UFP is sourcing Vbus (self-powered display)

An ordinary non-PD USB peripheral would not source Vbus back at the
DFP, so the combination is a reliable fingerprint for a passive DP
cable connected to a powered display.

When detected, call tcpm_mux_set() with TYPEC_DP_STATE_E (4-lane DP,
no USB SuperSpeed) directly, bypassing the VDM negotiation path that
will never succeed.

The sunxi-phy-switcher driver receives this call (data == NULL) and
synthesises HPD=asserted — see the companion patch to that driver —
which causes the combophy to fire its serdes extcon so edp0 starts
DisplayPort link training.

Signed-off-by: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c | 21 +++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c b/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c
--- a/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c
@@ -4197,6 +4197,27 @@ static void run_state_machine(struct tcpm_port *port)
 		 * possible when type-c is connected to Type-A/B
 		 */

+		/*
+		 * Passive USB-C→DisplayPort cable: pd_capable stays false
+		 * because the display has no PD controller (every
+		 * Source_Capabilities TX returns TCPC_TX_FAILED, no GoodCRC).
+		 * vbus_present is true because the self-powered display sources
+		 * 5 V on Vbus back through the cable.  This combination
+		 * reliably identifies the cable; an ordinary non-PD USB
+		 * peripheral would not source Vbus back at the DFP.  Switch
+		 * the mux to 4-lane DP (STATE_E) directly instead of waiting
+		 * for VDMs that will never come.
+		 */
+		if (!port->pd_capable && port->vbus_present) {
+			enum typec_orientation orientation;
+
+			if (port->polarity == TYPEC_POLARITY_CC1)
+				orientation = TYPEC_ORIENTATION_NORMAL;
+			else
+				orientation = TYPEC_ORIENTATION_REVERSE;
+			tcpm_mux_set(port, TYPEC_DP_STATE_E,
+				     USB_ROLE_HOST, orientation);
+		}
 		break;
